This paper involves the use of a multirotor-based aerial manipulator to interact with a moving structure, specifically a hinged door. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also involves computer vision techniques for detecting the door and its position, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of model predictive control (MPC) and differential dynamic programming (DDP) for generating position setpoints involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
